  "title": "Get total number of hits returned ",
  "body": "My main reason for wanting this, is to be able to display a \"no results\" template when there are no results. This would be very easy to do if I were able to keep track of the number of Hits returned, but I do not see this available after going through the docs. What I would like to do is something similar to this: \r\n\r\n```\r\nconst SearchVideo = React.createClass({\r\n  result({hit}) {\r\n    if (!hit) return null;\r\n    return (\r\n      <Highlight attributeName=\"title\" hit={hit} />\r\n    );\r\n  },\r\n\r\n  render() {\r\n    if(!this.props.active){ return <span/>; }\r\n    return (\r\n      <div className=\"w-clearfix\">\r\n        {\r\n          hits.length > 0? (\r\n            <Hits hitComponent={this.result}/>\r\n          ) : <NoResults />\r\n        }\r\n      </div>\r\n    )\r\n  }\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nAny help you could provide would be very helpful. ",
